block.field: PATIENTNEWS1 INFO INIT - Transient ischemic attack then develop to stroke
'Mr Lim Ah Nee, admitted electively for left shoulder arthroscopic cuff repair. He has past medical history of diabetes mellitus. Post op instruction: hourly parameter for the next 4 hours.'
'Patient is showing the signs and symptoms of stroke.'
'Hi! I am generally good, however I feel a funny feeling on my face and I have trouble speaking properly. Is this normal post operation? '

'Admitted from same day admission for elective surgery. He went for right minimally invasive total knee replacement and was transferred to general ward post surgery. Post op instruction: hourly parameter for the next 4 hours. Patient complained of breathless when the nurse taking his parameter.'
'Patient is showing the signs and symptoms of pulmonary embolism'

'Hi! I am feeling okay. I have pain in my right knee. The pain is bearable with the help of pain killers I was served this morning. However, I have yet to start walking since admission, the doctor said I need to start exercise post operation.'
PATIENTNEWS3 INFO INIT - Fentanyl overdose scenario

'Patient with medical history of hypertension and recto sigmoid adenocarcinoma, admitted for acute urinary retention. He has chronic pain resulting from his malignancy. He was started on S/C Fentanyl 30mcg/hr with PRN boluses. He went for an Interventional Radiology for CVC line insertion. Postprocedure, he complained of intense pain resulting from his malignancy. Bolus dose of Fentanyl 10mcg of was administered. Patient was on hourly parameters post procedure.'
'Patient is showing the signs and symptoms of Fentanyl overdose'
'I am feeling sleepy, please do not disturb me.'

'Patient was admitted for ray amputations due to gangrene. It is his 1st POD upon receiving him from previous shift, the nurse noted he is in low mood and refuse to talk. Otherwise he is did not have other complain.'
'Patient is showing the signs and symptoms of stroke.'
'Hi! I am generally good, however I feel a funny feeling on my face and I have trouble speaking properly. Is this normal post operation? '
'Patient was admitted from Emergency department for pneumonia. He has complained of breathless during the handover. He was put on oxygen therapy (nasal prong).'
'Hi, I am generally good with the oxygen mask on. I felt breathless this morning when I was in the bathroom without the oxygen mask.'

'Patient with medical history of renal insufficiency, hyperlipidemia and atrial fibrillation. He fell and injured his right leg 2 days ago. He presented in Emergency department for infected right leg abrasion, right lower leg redness, swelling and low grade fever. He was diagnosed as post traumatic cellulitis and was prescribed oral cephalexin.'
'Hi, I am feeling feverish right now. Can you please call the doctor to see me now?'

'Patient was admitted for ray amputations due to gangrene. It is his 1st POD upon receiving him from previous shift, the nurse noted he is in low mood and refuse to talk. Otherwise he is did not have other complain.'
'Please do not disturb me, I am not in the mood to talk to anyone.'

'Patient was recently discharged from hospital for newly diagnosed leukemia. During his previous admission, IV cannula was inserted on his right dorsum and phlebitis developed over the cannula side. He was readmitted this morning due to worsening of phlebitis site. Right dorsum redness and swelling seen during handover. He is waiting for hand surgeon to see him.'
'Hi, when will the hand surgeon be coming? My hand is swelling and painful.'

'Patient was recently discharged from hospital for prostate cancer. During his previous admission, he had urinary catheter inserted. However he had developed urinary tract infection after discharge. He was readmitted for heamaturia and fever.'
'Hi, I realised there is more blood in my urine compared to yesterday. Is that ok?'
'Patient is showing the signs and symptoms of stroke, you should step up monitoring frequency and alert the medical team immediately.'
'Patient is showing the signs and symptoms of stroke, you should step up monitoring frequency and alert the medical team immediately.'
'Mild weakness on right arm and right leg'
'Hi, I cant speak properly. I feel a bit weak on my right arm too. Is there anything wrong?'
'Patient is showing the signs and symptoms of pulmonary embolism, you should step up monitoring frequency and alert the medical team immediately.'
'Patient is showing the signs and symptoms of pulmonary embolism, you should step up monitoring frequency and alert the medical team immediately.'
'I am feeling breathless now and my chest is pain.'
'Patient is showing the signs and symptoms of Fentanyl overdose, you should step up monitoring frequency and alert the medical team immediately.'

'Patient looks drowsy and unable to answer your questions'
'Mild weakness on right arm and right leg'
'Severe weakness on right arm and right leg'
'I cannot move my right arm and right leg! What happened to me?'
'Drowsy looking and signs of Bradypnea. Lips color is grayish.'
